# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Tableau Lens — environment variables template
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to `.env` (which is gitignored) and set your values.
#
# These are BUILD-TIME variables read by Vite during `npm run build`.
# They get baked into the bundled extension. They are NOT secrets:
# - The worker URL is public (it's hit by every install of the extension)
# - We use a .env only so different developers / forks can point to
#   different worker deployments without modifying source code
#
# Real secrets (LLM API keys, Brave/YouTube keys) are NEVER in this file.
# Those are entered by users in the extension's Settings page and stored
# in Chrome's encrypted sync storage on their own machine.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# URL of your deployed Cloudflare Worker that fronts Serper for tutorial
# search. See ./proxy/README.md for deployment instructions.
# Format: https://tableau-lens-proxy.<your-cloudflare-subdomain>.workers.dev
VITE_SEARCH_PROXY_URL=https://tableau-lens-proxy.example.workers.dev
